'''''Bangalore Tiger: How Indian Tech upstart [[Wipro]] Is Rewriting the Rules of Global Competition''''' is a book published in 2006 by [[McGraw-Hill Companies]], Inc, [[New York City]], and authored by Steve Hamm. It focuses on what it calls the "new breed of transnationals" who have brought about cause for "multinationals" to "beware".

Says the book's jacket: "From its mastery of global collaboration and its market expansion strategy to its constant-improvement approach and "zero [[politics]]" policy, author Steve Hamm reveals the never-before-told story of how "The Wipro Way" of doing business is changing the world.

An [[India]]n edition of the book was published by [[Tata McGraw-Hill]] of [[New Delhi]]. It is dated 2007, though the book was available at [[newsstand]]s and [[bookshop]]s in end-2006.

