'''Remi Vermeiren''' (born 23 February 1940 in [[Dendermonde]]) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] banker and businessman.

==Education==
He went to high school at the Royal Athenaeum of Dendermonde and graduated as licentiate in commercial and financial sciences at the Hoger instituut voor Handels- en Bestuurswetenschapen in [[Brussels]] (evening education).

==Career==
He started his career at the [[KBC Group|Kredietbank]] (KBC), and became President of the board of directors of the [[KBC Group]] at the merger of KBC, ABB and CERA in 1998. He is a leading member of the business club [[De Warande (Club)|De Warande]]. He is a member of the board of [[Union Minière du Haut Katanga|Cumerio]] and since 2005 non-executive, independent director of [[DevGen]].

Remi Vermeiren is one of the authors of ''The manifesto for the separation of Belgium'' (Dutch: Het Manifest voor de opsplitsing van België) which was drafted by the [[think tank]] ''In De Warande''.

